STEP 1: Create Laravel Project

Open terminal:

composer create-project laravel/laravel simple-login
cd simple-login
php artisan serve

Open browser:

http://127.0.0.1:8000
 STEP 2: Setup Database Connection

Open .env file and change:

DB_DATABASE=login_db
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=

Now create database in MySQL:

CREATE DATABASE login_db;
STEP 3: Create Users Table (Very Basic)

Run this command:

php artisan make:migration create_users_table

Open migration file inside:
database/migrations/xxxx_create_users_table.php

Replace with this simple code:

public function up()
{
    Schema::create('users', function (Blueprint $table) {
        $table->id();
        $table->string('username');
        $table->string('password');
        $table->timestamps();
    });
}

Run migration:

php artisan migrate
 STEP 4: Insert Default Login Data (Important)

Open MySQL (phpMyAdmin or terminal):

INSERT INTO users (username, password) 
VALUES ('admin', '1234');

Now default login:

Username: admin

Password: 1234

 STEP 5: Create Controller (Login Logic)

Run:

php artisan make:controller LoginController

Open:
app/Http/Controllers/LoginController.php

Paste this beginner-friendly code:

<?php

namespace App\Http\Controllers;

use Illuminate\Http\Request;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

class LoginController extends Controller
{
    // Show Login Page
    public function index()
    {
        return view('login');
    }

    // Check Login
    public function checkLogin(Request $request)
    {
        $username = $request->username;
        $password = $request->password;

        // Check in database
        $user = DB::table('users')
            ->where('username', $username)
            ->where('password', $password)
            ->first();

        if ($user) {
            return redirect('/home'); // success page
        } else {
            return back()->with('error', 'Login Failed! Wrong Username or Password');
        }
    }

    // Next Page after login
    public function home()
    {
        return view('home');
    }
}
STEP 6: Create Routes (Very Important)

Open:
routes/web.php

Replace with:

use App\Http\Controllers\LoginController;

Route::get('/', [LoginController::class, 'index']);
Route::post('/login', [LoginController::class, 'checkLogin']);
Route::get('/home', [LoginController::class, 'home']);

This means:

/ → login page

/login → login check

/home → next page after success

STEP 7: Create Login Page (View)

Create file:
resources/views/login.blade.php

Paste:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple Login</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Login Form</h2>

<!-- Error Message -->
@if(session('error'))
    <p style="color:red;">{{ session('error') }}</p>
@endif

<form method="POST" action="/login">
    @csrf

    <label>Username:</label><br>
    <input type="text" name="username" required><br><br>

    <label>Password:</label><br>
    <input type="password" name="password" required><br><br>

    <button type="submit">Login</button>
</form>

</body>
</html>
STEP 8: Create Next Page (After Login Success)

Create file:
resources/views/home.blade.php

Paste:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Home Page</title>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Login Successful </h2>
<p>Welcome to Next Page (Home)</p>

</body>
</html>


FINAL TEST

Start server:

php artisan serve

Open:

http://127.0.0.1:8000
Correct Login:

Username: admin

Password: 1234
➡ Redirect to Home Page

Wrong Login:

Stay on same page

Show error: Login Failed!

